<item>
            <title>[JDK-8297757] VarHandles.getStaticFieldFromBaseAndOffset should get the receiver type from VarHandle</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8297757</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>A spin off from &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8294278&quot; title=&quot;ForkJoinPool.getAndAddPoolIds should use Unsafe.staticFieldBase&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8294278&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8294278&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The implementation of VarHandle::describeConstable for static fields uses VarHandles.getStaticFieldFromBaseAndOffset to map a base/offset/fieldType to a static Field. This assumes that the location of a static field returned by Unsafe.staticFieldBase is a Class object. It may need to be re-examined for this code to be usable with other VM implementations.</description>
